# Spec-Kit Process

Every feature follows this order — do not skip steps:

1. **Specify** — define what and why (`spec.md` with user stories + acceptance criteria)
2. **Clarify** — resolve ambiguities before planning
3. **Plan** — choose technical approach and architecture
4. **Tasks** — break into ordered, actionable steps (`tasks.md`)
5. **Implement** — build according to the plan, validate against the spec

# File Locations

```
Life App/
├── ROADMAP.md                          # Feature status overview
├── AGENT-ONBOARDING.md                 # Agent onboarding reference
├── .specify/
│   ├── memory/constitution.md          # Governing principles (highest authority)
│   └── specs/<feature>/
│       ├── spec.md                     # Feature specification
│       └── tasks.md                    # Implementation task list
└── specs/master/
    ├── data-model.md                   # Database schema reference
    ├── tasks.md                        # Completed work log
    └── contracts/api-routes.md         # All REST endpoints
```

# Project Structure

```
Life App/
├── src/
│   ├── app/                  # Next.js App Router pages + API routes
│   │   ├── api/              # All REST endpoints
│   │   └── (pages)/          # Page files — thin, delegate to components
│   ├── components/           # Feature components + shadcn/ui primitives
│   ├── db/                   # Drizzle schema, migrations, backup
│   ├── lib/                  # Pure logic (scheduler, periodization, utils)
│   │   └── __tests__/        # Vitest test files
│   ├── hooks/                # Custom React hooks
│   ├── scripts/              # One-off scripts (seed, migrate, backfill)
│   └── types/index.ts        # Shared TypeScript interfaces
```
